No new seashells.

582
00:46:28,386 --> 00:46:30,636
I gotta admit
I can't put my foot on it right now.

583
00:46:31,022 --> 00:46:33,712
- If l stand here long enough...
- She's got legs, you idiot.

584
00:46:34,158 --> 00:46:38,028
She traded her voice to the sea witch
and got legs. Geez, man.

585
00:46:38,629 --> 00:46:39,939
I knew that.

586
00:46:40,197 --> 00:46:41,897
Ariel's been turned into a human.

587
00:46:42,199 --> 00:46:45,979
She'll make the prince fall in love
with her, and he's gotta kiss her.

588
00:46:46,570 --> 00:46:49,850
And she's only got three days.

589
00:46:51,309 --> 00:46:53,059
Just look at her.

590
00:46:53,377 --> 00:46:55,957
On legs. On human legs.

591
00:46:57,548 --> 00:47:00,417
My nerves are shot.
This is a catastrophe.

592
00:47:00,885 --> 00:47:03,465
What would her father say?
I'll tell you what he'd say.

593
00:47:03,888 --> 00:47:06,788
He'd say he's gonna kill himself a crab.
That's what he'd say.

594
00:47:07,258 --> 00:47:09,808
I'm gonna march meself
straight home right now

595
00:47:10,227 --> 00:47:12,567
and tell him like 1 should have done
the minute...

596
00:47:12,963 --> 00:47:15,953
And don't you shake your head
at me, young lady.

597
00:47:16,434 --> 00:47:18,214
Maybe there's still time.

598
00:47:18,536 --> 00:47:21,056
If we could get that witch
to give you back your voice,

599
00:47:21,472 --> 00:47:24,432
you could go home
with all the normal fish and just be...

600
00:47:25,710 --> 00:47:28,110
just be...

601
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:33,112
just be miserable
for the rest of your life.

602
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:38,476
All right, all right.

603
00:47:38,923 --> 00:47:42,462
I'll try to help ya find that prince.

604
00:47:45,730 --> 00:47:49,540
Boy, what a soft shell
I'm turning out to be.

605
00:47:50,134 --> 00:47:51,914
Now, Ariel, I'm telling ya.

606
00:47:52,236 --> 00:47:56,238
If you wanna be a human, the first thing
ya gotta do is dress like one.

607
00:48:03,481 --> 00:48:05,941
Max? What?

608
00:48:06,951 --> 00:48:09,911
What? Max.

609
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:15,095
Ya look great, kid.
Ya look sensational.

610
00:48:28,305 --> 00:48:30,055
Max.

611
00:48:31,242 --> 00:48:32,582
Max.

612
00:48:32,843 --> 00:48:35,062
Quiet, Max.

613
00:48:35,446 --> 00:48:37,726
What's gotten into you, fella? Oh.

614
00:48:38,883 --> 00:48:40,633
Oh, I see.

615
00:48:42,887 --> 00:48:44,637
Are you OK, miss?

616
00:48:44,955 --> 00:48:47,005
I'm sorry if this knucklehead
scared you.

617
00:48:47,358 --> 00:48:49,288
He's harmless really.

618
00:48:51,562 --> 00:48:55,781
You seem very familiar to me.
Have we met?

619
00:48:59,036 --> 00:49:02,726
We have met. I knew it.
You're the one I've been looking for.

620
00:49:03,307 --> 00:49:05,357
What's your name?

621
00:49:06,710 --> 00:49:08,900
What's wrong? What is it?

622
00:49:10,948 --> 00:49:12,698
