641
00:50:39,637 --> 00:50:39,702
Eric, be reasonable.

642
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:41,403
Eric, be reasonable.

643
00:50:41,705 --> 00:50:46,275
Nice young ladies just don't swim around
rescuing people in the ocean

644
00:50:46,977 --> 00:50:48,727
and then flitter off into oblivion.

645
00:50:49,046 --> 00:50:51,006
I'm tellin’ ya, Grim.
She was real.

646
00:50:51,348 --> 00:50:54,278
I'm gonna find that girl,
and I'm gonna marry her.

647
00:50:55,152 --> 00:50:57,582
Come on, honey. Don't be shy.

648
00:51:05,396 --> 00:51:08,146
Eric, isn't she a vision?

649
00:51:10,167 --> 00:51:12,307
You look wonderful.

650
00:51:12,670 --> 00:51:16,540
Come, come. You must be famished.
Let me help you, my dear.

651
00:51:17,141 --> 00:51:19,251
There we go. That's better.

652
00:51:19,610 --> 00:51:22,950
Now, quite comfy? Good.

653
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:27,990
It's not often that we have
such a lovely dinner guest, eh, Eric?

654
00:51:41,165 --> 00:51:44,095
Do you like it? It is rather a fine one.

655
00:51:46,203 --> 00:51:47,903
Oh, my.

656
00:51:48,205 --> 00:51:49,815
Sorry, Grim.

657
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:54,207
Why, Eric, that's the first time
I've seen you smile in weeks.

658
00:51:54,845 --> 00:51:57,095
Very amusing.

659
00:51:57,481 --> 00:51:59,441
Carlotta, my dear, what's for dinner?

660
00:51:59,783 --> 00:52:04,442
You're gonna love it. Chef's been fixing
his speciality: stuffed crab.

661
00:52:07,191 --> 00:52:10,060
Nouvelle cuisine

662
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:12,227
,
Les Champs-Elysées

663
00:52:12,529 --> 00:52:15,599
Maurice Chevalier

664
00:52:18,102 --> 00:52:20,622
Les poissons, les poissons

665
00:52:21,038 --> 00:52:22,648
How I love les poissons

