Love to chop and to serve little fish

667
00:52:26,343 --> 00:52:29,533
First l cut off their heads
Then I pull out their bones

668
00:52:30,047 --> 00:52:33,037
Mais oui, ¢a c'est toujours delish

669
00:52:33,517 --> 00:52:35,267
Les poissons, les poissons

670
00:52:37,154 --> 00:52:40,114
With the cleaver I hack them in two

671
00:52:40,591 --> 00:52:43,221
! pull out what's inside
and I serve it up fried

672
00:52:43,661 --> 00:52:46,561
‘Cause I love little fishes
Don't you?

673
00:52:47,031 --> 00:52:50,191
Here's something for tempting the palate

674
00:52:50,701 --> 00:52:52,661
Prepared in the classic technique

675
00:52:53,003 --> 00:52:56,073
First you pound the fish flat
with the mallet

676
00:52:56,573 --> 00:52:59,703
Then you slash through the skin,
give the belly a slice

677
00:53:00,210 --> 00:53:01,790
Then you rub some salt in

678
00:53:02,079 --> 00:53:05,359
‘Cause that makes it taste nice

679
00:53:07,918 --> 00:53:10,228
l have missed one.

680
00:53:10,621 --> 00:53:12,491
Sacrebleu
What is this

681
00:53:12,823 --> 00:53:14,133
How on earth could! miss

682
00:53:14,391 --> 00:53:17,231
Such a sweet, little succulent crab?

683
00:53:17,695 --> 00:53:19,155
Quel dommage
What a loss

684
00:53:19,430 --> 00:53:20,690
Here we go, in the sauce

685
00:53:20,931 --> 00:53:23,511
Now some flour
I think just a dab

686
00:53:23,934 --> 00:53:25,774
Now I'll stuff you with bread

687
00:53:26,103 --> 00:53:29,853
It don't hurt ‘cause you're dead
and you're certainly lucky you are

688
00:53:30,441 --> 00:53:32,841
‘Cause it's gonna be hot
in my big silver pot

689
00:53:33,243 --> 00:53:36,283
Toodle-oo
Mon poisson, au revoir

690
00:53:43,520 --> 00:53:46,150
What is this?

691
00:54:15,786 --> 00:54:19,736
I think I'd better go see
what Louis is up to.

692
00:54:22,326 --> 00:54:25,866
Come out, you little pipsqueak,
and fight like a man.

693
00:54:26,430 --> 00:54:28,710
Louis.

694
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:33,519
- What are you doing?
- Well, I was just...

695
00:54:34,204 --> 00:54:36,604
I'm sorry, madame.

696
00:54:38,509 --> 00:54:41,089
You know, Eric,
perhaps our young guest might enjoy

697
00:54:41,512 --> 00:54:43,792
